<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.01/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-11T10:00:00-05:00">September 11, 1930—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:35 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>202. My 201, September 10, 8 p.m. Paraguay has accorded recognition; and
                            I understand the British Chargé d’Affaires, French Minister, and Papal
                            Nuncio have recommended to their respective Governments that recognition
                            be given. The German Minister may do the same.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>